The Agriculture Department recalled 14,000 jars of 4-ounce Vegetable due to potential contamination.
Heinz also faced a recall in Hong Kong.
Sara Lee Corp. recalled hot dogs after a food poisoning outbreak.
No illnesses have been linked to the recalled products.
Listeria outbreaks are a growing concern, prompting more testing.
The FDA recommends thorough cooking and proper food handling.
IBP recalled ground beef due to E.coli concerns.
The recall affected 33 states.
Overall, food safety remains a critical issue requiring vigilance and swift action.
